It's the 13th day of the national lockdown and police have been on the streets – making sure only essential service workers are driving around. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced almost two weeks ago that only essential travel would be permitted. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police are out on the streets making sure only essential service workers are driving around. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced almost two weeks ago that only essential travel would be permitted. WATCH: Motorists taking chances with the law during lockdown Essential service workers are required to travel with our ID documents and permits. READ: COVID-19: Five more deaths reported in South Africa Every vehicle going in both directions on this busy road – is stopped and checked. Officers say those who can't explain where they're going – or produce essential service worker permits – are given heavy fines. Jail time is also possible. Watch the video above for more on the story.